    "title": "Bailout Protocol: Mandatory Human Accountability in Multi-Agent Hierarchical Systems",
    "publication_date": "2026-04-24",
    "description": "The Bailout Protocol defines the mandatory human accountability mechanism required when autonomous agents encounter situations exceeding their bounded operational scope. We formalize the bailout trigger as a constraint-satisfaction boundary event, establishing the protocols, priority escalation paths, and audit requirements for human review and intervention. This ensures no autonomous system action proceeds beyond designated boundaries without explicit human authorization.",
